annotation.text: Description: The purpose of this subrocess is to validate the payload data based on the business rules specified in the Suitable Operator FDD 2.0 Author: Dejan Kovac Date Created: 16/12/2014 Date Modified:

Business Rules for the individual applicant data validation:
1. Type must be provided if Customer Reference number is not provided (Error 10) 2. Title can be optional i.e "blank" or if provided it must must be provided if customer reference is not provided (Error 12) 3. First Name must be provided if Type is IND i.e individual (Error 13) 4. Surname must be provided if Type is IND (Error 14) 5. Date of Birth must be provided if Type is IND and it cannot be in the future (Error 15) 6. Registration cannot be done if the status is REG status(Error 60)

Business Rules for the organisation applicant data validation:
1. Business Name must be provided if the party name is Org type with the code CMP or ARB (Error 17) 2. Business Number Type must be provided if the party name is Org type with the code CMP or ARB and has to be of the valid type
